On Thu, 24 May 2007, Mike Soultanian wrote:

> ...Make sure you do NOT use
> brake fluid that has been opened already.  Once you open it, you can
> only store it for about a month and then it's trash as it absorbs water
> out of the air.

It is true that the fluid will absorb water from the air, but as long as
the container is kept sealed it won't absorb a significant amount of
water.  Leave it open for a few days and you'll have a problem.
